libmikmod
-------------------------------------------
The MikMod sound library is an excellent way for a programmer to add 
music and sound effects to an application. It is a powerful and flexible 
library, with a simple and easy-to-learn API. 

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-15

Build requirements:
  autoconf2.5-2.63-1
  automake1.5-1.5-3
  binutils-20080624-2
  cygport-0.4.3-1
  gawk-3.1.6-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  libtool-2.2.6a-1
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical homepage:
  http://mikmod.raphnet.net/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libmikmod-3.1.12-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libmikmod-3.1.12.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libmikmod-3.1.12-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libmikmod-devel-3.1.12.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libmikmod2-3.1.12.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary packages:

(libmikmod2)
  /usr/bin/cygmikmod-2.dll
  /usr/share/doc/libmikmod-3.1.12/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libmikmod-3.1.12/COPYING.LIB
  /usr/share/doc/libmikmod-3.1.12/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/libmikmod-3.1.12/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/libmikmod-3.1.12/README
  /usr/share/doc/libmikmod-3.1.12/TODO

(libmikmod-devel)
  /usr/bin/libmikmod-config
  /usr/include/mikmod.h
  /usr/lib/libmikmod.a
  /usr/lib/libmikmod.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libmikmod.la
  /usr/share/aclocal/libmikmod.m4
  /usr/share/info/mikmod.info.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/libmikmod-config.1.gz

------------------

Port Notes:

----- version 3.1.12-1 -----
Version bump.  Fixed OSS driver.

----- version 3.1.11-2 -----
Rebuilt for cygport with several Gentoo patches.
Created separate lib and devel packages.

----- version 3.1.11-1 -----
Initial release for Cygwin.
Includes the 3.1.11-a patches from the author's website.


